{"type":"step-attempt","step":"spec-review","sessionId":"2a6b2a3d-fc79-4e20-97c4-35f829621c1b","outcome":{"verdict":"approved","findingsPath":"specrunner/changes/bite-test-executor/spec-review-result-001.md","error":null,"toolResult":{"ok":true,"approved":true,"findings":[],"observations":[{"severity":"low","file":"tasks.md","title":"T5 gate test needs forward-type request state (FORWARD_TYPES constraint)","rationale":"runBiteEvidenceGate returns strategy-deferred immediately for non-forward types. T5 must use request.type = 'bug-fix' or 'new-feature' in the job state. tasks.md says 'follow existing gate/floor test state shape' without naming this constraint explicitly. An implementer reading gate.ts would find it, but an explicit note reduces risk."},{"severity":"low","file":"tasks.md","title":"scopedTestCommand trust boundary not documented","rationale":"scopedTestCommand is passed as-is to sh -c, same as verification.commands. The project-author trust boundary is the same, so no new attack surface is introduced, but design.md does not explicitly state this equivalence. testFile shell-quoting is documented; scopedTestCommand's trust model is not."},{"severity":"low","file":"tasks.md","title":"No acceptance criterion for testFile paths with special characters","rationale":"The single-quote escaping algorithm for testFile is specified in T-02 but T4's acceptance criteria do not include a case with spaces or single quotes in the file path to verify the escaping works end-to-end. Low risk in practice (git-managed paths rarely contain special chars), but the gap exists."}]},"followUpAttempts":0,"transientRetryAttempts":0,"addedTurns":{"reportRetry":0,"postWork":0,"outputRepair":0}},"startedAt":"2026-07-17T18:35:31.173Z","endedAt":"2026-07-17T18:40:17.364Z","commitOid":"e55bd55812dc5c18d13c128465d3e235da7515ed"}
